    "Description": "Bouncers attack one tile in front of them, much like aHornetwithout flight. What differentiates the Bouncer is that it will push the target tile and push themselves back by 1 tile, potentially resulting in a chain of collisions.",
    "Strategy": "Bouncers are easy to deal with in open spaces, as they can be pushed away from targets much like aScorpion. However, the two-directional push must be considered as it could lead to further damage on grid buildings; this can be used to your advantage by directing the backwards push into a mountain or water tile. In the latter, they will instantly drown and be destroyed."
