  "full_text": "Bouncer\nDetails\nHealth\n3\nMove\n3\nSystems\nEnergized Horns\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nDeal 1 damage to the target then bounce backwards.\nThe\nBouncer\nis a common\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\nintroduced in the Advanced Edition. They are only present if Advanced Enemies are turned on at the start of a new timeline.\nDescription\n[\n]\nBouncers attack one tile in front of them, much like a\nHornet\nwithout flight. What differentiates the Bouncer is that it will push the target tile and push themselves back by 1 tile, potentially resulting in a chain of collisions.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nBouncers are easy to deal with in open spaces, as they can be pushed away from targets much like a\nScorpion\n. However, the two-directional push must be considered as it could lead to further damage on grid buildings; this can be used to your advantage by directing the backwards push into a mountain or water tile. In the latter, they will instantly drown and be destroyed.\nv\n\u00b7\nd\n\u00b7\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n\u2022\nBlobber\n\u2022\nBurrower\n\u2022\nCentipede\n\u2022\nCrab\n\u2022\nDigger\n\u2022\nFirefly\n\u2022\nHornet\n\u2022\nLeaper\n\u2022\nScarab\n\u2022\nScorpion\n\u2022\nSpider\n\u2022\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n\u2022\nGastropod\n\u2022\nMosquito\n\u2022\nMoth\n\u2022\nPlasmodia\n\u2022\nStarfish\n\u2022\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n\u2022\nAlpha Blobber\n\u2022\nAlpha Burrower\n\u2022\nAlpha Centipede\n\u2022\nAlpha Crab\n\u2022\nAlpha Digger\n\u2022\nAlpha Firefly\n\u2022\nAlpha Hornet\n\u2022\nAlpha Leaper\n\u2022\nAlpha Scarab\n\u2022\nAlpha Scorpion\n\u2022\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n\u2022\nAlpha Gastropod\n\u2022\nAlpha Mosquito\n\u2022\nAlpha Moth\n\u2022\nAlpha Plasmodia\n\u2022\nAlpha Starfish\n\u2022\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n\u2022\nBlood Psion\n\u2022\nShell Psion\n\u2022\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n\u2022\nRaging Psion\n\u2022\nSmol